<p>
  <span class="nym">Rubeus</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>rubeus</i> 'red'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>Even as late as the third quarter of the 15th C, the etymological origin of the name was still known.  In <span class="bibl"><span class="key">RCCaetani6</span>, <span class="loc">2720</span></span>, the same man is recorded as both <i>Rubeus</i> and <i>Russius</i> (cf. <a class="nym" href="Rosso">Rosso</a>).</p>
<p></p>
</div>
  


